netic Complexity of Nitrogen Fixation</strong><br>\n    Microbiology 1984. <strong>130:</strong> 2745-2755. <nobr><a href=\"/mic/cgi/reprint/130/11/2745\">[PDF]</a></nobr></dd>\n  </dl>\n  <p></p>\n  <dl>\n    <dt>Milton R. J. Salton</dt>\n    <dd><strong>The Sixteenth Marjory Stephenson Memorial Lecture</strong><br>\n    Microbiology 1983. <strong>129:</strong> 2685-2702. <nobr><a href=\"/mic/cgi/reprint/129/9/2685\">[PDF]</a></nobr></dd>\n  </dl>\n  <p></p>\n  <dl>\n    <dt>BRIAN G. SPRATT</dt>\n    <dd><strong>Penicillin-binding Proteins and the Future of β-Lactam Antibiotics: The Seventh Fleming Lecture</strong><br>\n    Microbiology 1983. <strong>129:</strong> 1247-1260. <nobr><a href=\"/mic/cgi/reprint/129/5/1247\">[PDF]</a></nobr></dd>\n  </dl>\n  <p></p>\n  <dl>\n    <dt>D. J. Sherratt</dt>\n    <dd><strong>The Maintenance and Propagation of Plasmid Genes in Bacterial Populations The Sixth Fleming Lecture</strong><br>\n    Microbiology 1982. <strong>128:</strong> 655-661. <nobr><a href=\"/mic/cgi/reprint/128/4/655\">[PDF]</a></nobr></dd>\n  </dl>\n  <p></p>\n  <dl>\n    <dt>PATRICIA H. CLARKE</dt>\n    <dd><strong>Adaptation The Fifteenth Marjory Stephenson Memorial Lecture</strong><br>\n    Microbiology 1981. <strong>126:</strong> 5-20. <nobr><a href=\"/mic/cgi/reprint/126/1/5\">[PDF]</a></nobr></dd>\n  </dl>\n  <p></p>\n  <dl>\n    <dt>FRANK E. YOUNG</dt>\n    <dd><strong>Impact of Cloning in <i>Bacillus subtilis</i> on Fundamental and Industrial Microbiology: The Eighth Griffith Memorial Lecture</strong><br>\n    Microbiology 1980. <strong>119:</strong> 1-15. <nobr><a href=\"/mic/cgi/reprint/119/1/1\">[PDF]</a></nobr></dd>\n  </dl>\n  <p></p>\n  <dl>\n    <dt>J. E. Beringer</dt>\n    <dd><strong>The Development of Rhizobium Genetics: The Fourth Fleming Lecture</strong><br>\n    Microbiology 1980. <strong>116:</strong> 1-7. <nobr><a href=\"/mic/cgi/reprint/116/1/1\">[PDF]</a></nobr></dd>\n  </dl>\n  <p></p>\n  <dl>\n    <dt>G. A. M. Cross</dt>\n    <dd><st